               <msContents>
                  <summary>In Minasian collection, there are 19 manuscripts under the generic title of Adʿīyah [Prayers]. The reason is that their individual titles have remained unknown for different reasons, including defective incipits and explicits.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_745-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note type="content-genre">Prayers</note>
                     <author key="person_f407">
                        <persName xml:lang="en" role="scr" change="#role-assignment">Anonymous</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2976">[Adʿīyah]</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_2976">[ادعیه]</title>
                     <note xml:lang="en">A collection of prayers, including for amulets and phylacteries (scattered pieces, also survived from various books, but mostly prayer books).</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" defective="true">… العنهم فی مستر السر و ظاهر العلانیه فی ارضک…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true">… و یعسوب الدین ابی الحسن علی بن ابی طالب علیه الف الف صلوة و الف الف سلام. تمت</explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="en">None.</colophon>
                     <listBibl>
                        <head>Sequence Number in the Persian Catalogue:</head><bibl>FAW 48</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
